    {
      "id": "u-s-power-system-signals-2024-2027",
      "title": "U.S. Power System Signals (2024-2027)",
      "intent": "table-analysis",
      "content": "| Indicator | 2024 | 2025 | 2026 | 2027 |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| U.S. electricity demand growth | 2.1% | 2.3% | 2.2% | 3.0%* |\n| U.S. data center electricity use (TWh) | ~180 | n/a | n/a | n/a |\n| U.S. electricity use growth (EIA STEO) | n/a | n/a | 1.0% | 3.0% |\n| Natural gas generation share (EIA) | n/a | 40% | 39% | 39% |\n| Wind generation share (EIA) | n/a | 11% | 11% | 12% |\n- *2027 figure from EIA Jan 2026 STEO press release.\n- Signal consistency across IEA and EIA supports a sustained demand-up regime.",
      "layout_slug": "table-insights-two-column",
      "variant": "white",
      "expected_slides": 1,
